The paper introduces a technique to capture the activation patterns of hidden layers in a Deep Neural Network for classification tasks. This is a common topic in the fields of machine learning and computer vision, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of statistical measures to compute the deviation of test samples from the typical activation patterns, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
